  "texts": [
    "The economic cost of these macroporous networks are ≈10-20× lower than commercial SERS substrates and may be further optimized for MP sensing by adapting the deposition method to work on cheaper foam substrates such as nickel, conductive polymers or custom 3D printed substrates that could also enhance both light absorbance and MP trapping (Suppl. Fig.",
    "41, Suppl.",
    "Table 8, and Suppl.",
    "To demultiplex information about MP chemical structure from the dataset, we designed a NN called SpecATNet to analyze patterns in the SERS survey spectra and identify MPs.",
    "SpecATNet borrows imagelike processing algorithms from CNNs that use pixels as input."
  ]
}